div.div: Launching multiple Kafka brokers fails - Configured brokerId doesn't match stored brokerId

Edit config/serverTest.properties and replace the existing config values as follows: broker.id=2 listeners=PLAINTEXT://9093 (1 more line was trimmed) If you want a third broker: cp config/server.properties config/server3.properties Edit config/server3.properties and replace the existing config values as follows: broker.id=3 listeners=PLAINTEXT://:9094 (1 more line was trimmed) if you run on different machines you must change advertised.listeners=PLAINTEXT://192.168.x.x: else if you run in the same vmware machine, for example you should only change the port and log.dir as described above
